OL,3,CBritain's seaside hotspots where house
OL,4,Cprices are growing fastest revealed
OL,6,FHouse prices in Penarth, a Welsh town
OL,7,Fnear to the capital Cardiff, were up
OL,8,Fby 8% to an average of #433,091 ` the
OL,9,Fhighest of the top 10 fastest-growing
OL,10,Fspots and the only one to sit above
OL,11,Fthe national average.
OL,13,FThe UK average price of a property
OL,14,Fcoming to the market in May was
OL,15,F#378,304, according to Rightmove.
OL,17,FAverage asking prices are currently
OL,18,F0.3% lower in Britain compared with
OL,19,Flast year, showing how some seaside
OL,20,Flocations are defying the dip and
OL,21,Foutpacing the nationwide market.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
